{
  "text": "One can view the proposed method as an extension of the hierarchical oct-tree representation used by Laur and Hanrahan [CITATION_1] . They introduced a first order representation (mip-map) and assembled the whole tree before the rendering of the basis function foot prints onto the image plane. The contributions of this work, compared to the mip-map, is that",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "17841832"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "17841832": {
      "title": "Hierarchical splatting: A progressive refinement algorithm for volume rendering",
      "abstract": "This paper presents a progressive refinement algorithm for volume rendering which uses a pyramidal volume representation. Besides storing average values, the pyramid stores estimated error, so an octtree can be fit to the pyramid given a user-supplied precision. This octtree is then drawn using a set of splats, or footprints, each scaled to match the size of the projection of a cell. The splats themselves are approximated with RGBA Gouraud-shaded polygons, so that they can be drawn efficiently on modern graphics workstations. The result is a real-time rendering algorithm suitable for interactive applications."
    }
  }
}